14/01/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- US Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Stuart Jones visited Pristina on Tuesday (January 13th) and assured leaders that policy towards Kosovo will not change under the new administration of incoming President Barack Obama. 
Kosovo presidential spokesman Xhavit Beqiri said Jones promised further support and co-operation.
In other news, police on Tuesday arrested six people suspected of involvement in corruption, organised crime and smuggling. 
The operation followed several months of investigation into smuggling and organised crime in the Mitrovica region. 
(Zeri, Express, Koha Ditore - 14/01/09; RTK, Telegrafi, Kohavision - 13/01/09)
